default font size of browser is 16 pixel i.e root is 16 pixel i.e html document font size is 16 pixel
rem is relative to the root element where as the em is relative to the parent element

html{
font-size:16px
}
rem value will gets changed based on the root of the document.

<div class="em">2m
<div class="em">4m
<div class="em">6m
<div class="em">8m
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="rem">2m
<div class="rem">2m
<div class="rem">2m
<div class="rem">2m
</div>
</div>
</div>
</div>

Why to use rem over pixels?

If we mention in pixels it is fixed to that perticular size only even though you change the font sizes from small to very large
but as rem is relative to the root element (which is html doc) this will get adjusted based on the font sizes we looking for 
